Honda Motor Co. Ltd. said on Thursday that it had  agreed on the terms and conditions for terminating its cross-shareholding  relationship with British carmaker Rover Group Ltd.
Under the agreement, which follows the purchase of 80 percent of Rover by  German carmaker Bayerishe Motoren Werke AG (BMW), Honda said it would  relinquish its 20 percent stake in Rover.
At the same time, the British carmaker would sell its 20 percent stake in  Honda of the UK Manufacturing Ltd. back to the Japanese carmaker.
"The other collaborative arrangements, including licensed production by  Rover of the Rover 600 and the replacement for the Rover 200-400 series, will  remain effective under the terms that have now been agreed," a statement said.
Honda said the agreement was reached on Wednesday.
